.el .ds Aq '
.TH webp-explain 1  "explain " 
.SH NAME
explain \- Explain an exit code: what a failing run\*(Aqs status number means
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBexplain\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fICODE\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Explain an exit code: what a failing run\*(Aqs status number means
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fICODE\fR>
An exit code (`0`..`9`) or its short name (`usage`, `limit`, ...)
